In [[mathematics]], the '''Manin–Drinfeld theorem''', proved by {{harvs|txt|last=Manin|year=1972|authorlink=Yuri I. Manin}} and {{harvs|txt|last=Drinfeld|authorlink=Vladimir Drinfeld|year=1973}}, states that the difference of two [[Cusp (singularity)|cusps]] of a [[modular curve]] has finite order in the [[Jacobian variety]].

