In computers, a '''serial decimal''' numeric representation is one in which ten [[bit]]s are reserved for each digit, with a different bit turned on depending on which of the ten possible digits is intended. [[ENIAC]] and [[CALDIC]] used this representation.<ref>[http://www.tjhsst.edu/~prittman/arch/Chap1/Chap1Old.html tjhsst.edu]</ref>
